# Fluff Date: 2026-03-13 20:44:32
<overview>
<p>The Black Wolf is a heavy class battle armor developed jointly by the scientist castes of Clan Wolf and Clan Wolf-in-Exile. Entering production in 3138, the suit was designed for close-in assault and support roles, configurable across multiple weapon loadouts to match mission requirements. Built on a Clan technology base, the design prioritizes heavy armor protection and durability over speed, giving it the staying power expected of a front-line Clan combat platform. Despite the complications that arose from its dual-origin development, the Black Wolf earned a reputation as a flexible and capable suit in the hands of both Clans.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At 1,500 kilograms, the Black Wolf trades speed for protection and hitting power. Ground movement is limited to ten kilometers per hour, but integrated jump jets allow thirty-meter bounds to close with targets. A right-arm Heavy Battle Claw enables OmniMech transport and delivers crushing strikes in close quarters. The suit carries 385 kilograms of reactive armor, granting strong resistance to explosive ordnance and missile fire at the cost of reduced protection against direct-fire energy weapons.</p><p>The ER Small Pulse Laser configuration mounts a Clan-manufactured extended range small pulse laser on the left arm modular weapon point. Pulse technology and extended range optics provide accurate fire at short to medium distances, while energy-based operation eliminates ammunition dependency. This makes the ERSPL loadout well-suited to sustained engagements and extended patrols where resupply may be uncertain. The lack of area-effect capability limits its usefulness against massed conventional infantry.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>Clan Wolf and Clan Wolf-in-Exile both deployed the ER Small Pulse Laser configuration in standard five-trooper Points. The energy weapon freedom from resupply concerns made this loadout a favored choice for reconnaissance-in-force missions and extended patrol rotations where logistical support was limited. Points equipped with this configuration often screened for heavier formations, using their sustained firepower to pin opponents for follow-up strikes by OmniMech Stars.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Black Wolf grew from a rare collaboration between the scientist castes of Clan Wolf and Clan Wolf-in-Exile. Beginning around 3134, researchers from both factions pooled resources to create a heavy battle armor that might serve as a bridge toward reunification. Production lines opened at WC Site 2 on Arc-Royal, W-7 Facilities on Weingarten, and later at Corean Enterprises MacAdams-Suharno on Stewart. The suit debuted in 3138, but the political hopes it carried were short-lived. When Khan Seth Ward allied with the Lyran Commonwealth and carved the Wolf Empire from its territory, the Black Wolf became a source of bitter division rather than unity.</p><p>The suit gained widespread attention during the invasion of Tharkad in 3143, where embedded Lyran media captured images of Black Wolf troopers storming fortified positions in the Triad district. For Clan Wolf-in-Exile and their Lyran allies, the armor they had helped create became an object of dread. Despite this fraught history, both halves of Clan Wolf continued fielding the Black Wolf in significant numbers. Clan Wolf-in-Exile assigned the suit to its touman out of necessity, while Clan Wolf Elementals embraced it eagerly. Divergences in production protocols between the Arc-Royal and Weingarten facilities rendered parts from the two lines incompatible, a practical complication that mirrored the political rift between the Clans.</p>
</history>

